I'm trying to use CloudinaryDotNet (Cloudinary .NET SDK) to delete resources that has a created date older than a specific date and has a specific prefix (the beginning of a public id if I understand things correctly). I haven't found any really good way of doing this.  So far I have come up with a solution where I have to list all the resources 500 at a time, since that is the maximum of resources returned by the method ListResources. When I have gathered the public ids of the resources I want removed I delete them using the method DeleteResources.
